<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 28 at 2:25PM MDT  by NWS Saltlake</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of south central
Millard...northwestern Piute...southwestern Sevier and northeastern
Beaver Counties through 300 PM MDT...
At 225 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Cove Fort, or 18 miles north of Beaver, moving north at 10 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and half inch hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Cove Fort.
This includes the following highways...
Interstate 15 between mile markers 125 and 140.
Interstate 70 between mile markers 0 and 9.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.50 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
